2. env DISPLAY=:0.0 your-gui-script

20 17 * * * env DISPLAY=:0.0 /home/jusss/lab/notifier.py hello test
this will work fine!
you need to give environment variable to cron

http://stackoverflow.com/questions/17518073/trying-to-run-a-python-script-from-ubuntu-crontab

Make the scripts executable
~$chmod +x script.py

You have to enable X ACL for localhost to connect to for GUI applications to work
~$ xhost +local:

Add the following line in the crontab "env DISPLAY=:0.0"
* * * * * env DISPLAY=:0.0 /usr/bin/python /your-script-somewhere.py

And one more line to crontab ">/dev/null 2>&1"
* * * * * env DISPLAY=:0.0 /usr/bin/python /your-script-somewhere.py >/dev/null 2>&1

you can check errors in /var/log/syslog file
~$ tail -20 /var/log/syslog

more info:
https://help.ubuntu.com/community/CronHowto
----------------------------------------------------------------------
/etc/systemd/system/battery.notifier.service
[Unit]
Description=Battery Notifier
### run after dnsmasq, because when I open dnsmasq after Xorg by hand, and it ne
eds Xorg
After=dnsmasq.service

[Service]
Type=simple
Environment="DISPLAY=:0.0"
ExecStart=/usr/bin/python3 /home/jusss/lab/battery.eeepc.py
# RestartSec=60
# TimeoutStartSec=120
Restart=no

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

